# Day 14 – Python String Methods Practice

Today I revised important Python string methods, understood their meanings, and practiced problems using each method.

---

# 1. capitalize()

## Meaning
Converts first character into uppercase.

## Example

```python
s = "python"

print(s.capitalize())
```

## Output

```text
Python
```

---

# 2. upper()

## Meaning
Converts entire string into uppercase.

## Example

```python
s = "python"

print(s.upper())
```

## Output

```text
PYTHON
```

---

# 3. lower()

## Meaning
Converts entire string into lowercase.

## Example

```python
s = "PYTHON"

print(s.lower())
```

## Output

```text
python
```

---

# 4. title()

## Meaning
Converts first character of every word into uppercase.

## Example

```python
s = "hello world"

print(s.title())
```

## Output

```text
Hello World
```

---

# 5. swapcase()

## Meaning
Uppercase becomes lowercase and lowercase becomes uppercase.

## Example

```python
s = "PyThOn"

print(s.swapcase())
```

## Output

```text
pYtHoN
```

---

# 6. count()

## Meaning
Counts occurrences of a character or word.

## Problem
Count how many times `"m"` appears.

## Example

```python
s = "programming"

print(s.count("m"))
```

## Output

```text
2
```

---

# 7. find()

## Meaning
Finds position (index) of character.

## Problem
Find index of `"t"`.

## Example

```python
s = "python"

print(s.find("t"))
```

## Output

```text
2
```

---

# 8. replace()

## Meaning
Replaces old character/string with new one.

## Problem
Replace `"h"` with `"y"`.

## Example

```python
s = "hello"

print(s.replace("h", "y"))
```

## Output

```text
yello
```

---

# 9. split()

## Meaning
Splits string into list of words.

## Problem
Split sentence into words.

## Example

```python
s = "python is easy"

print(s.split())
```

## Output

```text
['python', 'is', 'easy']
```

---

# 10. join()

## Meaning
Joins list elements into single string.

## Problem
Join all words using spaces.

## Example

```python
words = ["python", "is", "easy"]

print(" ".join(words))
```

## Output

```text
python is easy
```

---

# 11. strip()

## Meaning
Removes spaces from both sides.

## Problem
Remove extra spaces.

## Example

```python
s = "   python   "

print(s.strip())
```

## Output

```text
python
```

---

# 12. lstrip()

## Meaning
Removes spaces from left side.

## Example

```python
s = "   python"

print(s.lstrip())
```

## Output

```text
python
```

---

# 13. rstrip()

## Meaning
Removes spaces from right side.

## Example

```python
s = "python   "

print(s.rstrip())
```

## Output

```text
python
```

